34. A bank shall approach the Central Registrar of Co-operative Societies (CRCS) or
Registrar of Co-operative Societies (RCS), as the case may be, for amendment in
its bye-laws after getting NOC from the concerned office of RBI. Once the approval
is obtained from CRCS / RCS, the bank shall apply to the concerned Regional
Office of RBI with the following documents:
(1) approval of Board of Directors;
(2) approval of General Body of the bank;
(3) amended bye-laws as approved by CRCS / RCS;
